      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA software must have documented verification tests and version control consistent with Model Risk Level 3 requirements.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R1 used under an FDA-recognized software quality plan; verification test suite results archived and traceable to solver version. Achieved level meets required level for Model Risk Level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver benchmarks against analytical solutions for beam bending and contact mechanics must demonstrate < 1% error at the element densities used.",
      "rationale": "Cantilever beam and Hertzian contact benchmark problems solved; errors < 0.4% at mesh densities used in the pedicle screw model. Code verification requirement satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate < 2% change in construct stiffness and yield load between the production mesh and a 1.5x refined mesh.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation performed on three mesh densities (coarse, medium, fine). Stiffness change between medium and fine: 1.1%; yield load change: 0.8%. Grid convergence index < 2% confirms discretization error is controlled."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals must converge below 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error must be < 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson convergence monitored across all 47 load steps; maximum force residual 3.2e-8; energy balance error 0.03%. Solver error is negligible relative to other uncertainty sources."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model setup must be reviewed by an independent analyst; boundary condition application and material assignment must be documented and checked against the simulation plan.",
      "rationale": "Independent analyst review completed per simulation plan SP-2023-047. Boundary conditions, contact definitions, and titanium alloy material properties independently verified. No use errors identified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model selection and geometric representation must be justified relative to the physics of quasi-static compression-bending of metallic spinal constructs.",
      "rationale": "Isotropic linear elasticity with Ti-6Al-4V properties used for screw and rod; nonlinear geometric effects (large displacement) activated. Justification documented: strain levels remain in elastic regime for the QoIs of interest. Model form appropriate for the intended prediction scope."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric dimensions must be traceable to measured values with uncertainty bounds reported; sensitivity analysis must identify dominant inputs.",
      "rationale": "Young's modulus and yield strength sourced from ASTM F136 certificates for the production lot; nominal geometry from CAD with dimensional inspection tolerance ±0.05 mm. One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis shows stiffness most sensitive to rod diameter (±3.2%). Input uncertainty propagated to QoI uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental sample set must be representative of the production device; N ≥ 10 constructs required; sample traceability to production lot documented.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs from two production lots tested across two independent laboratories. Dimensional inspection confirms conformance to design drawings. Sample traceability documented in test report TR-2022-F1717-001. Requirement met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing must cover the range of loading conditions relevant to the COU; multiple test configurations or load levels required to characterize model behavior across the operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single load configuration (5° offset, 10 mm spacer block per ASTM F1717). No additional load levels or construct configurations tested. Achieved level is below required level; this gap is acknowledged and accepted based on the standard nature of the F1717 protocol and the conservative single-condition characterization."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters must be mapped to experimental conditions with documented equivalency; any discrepancies must be quantified.",
      "rationale": "Fixture geometry, load application point, and boundary conditions in the FEA replicate the physical test setup as confirmed by overlay comparison. Material properties derived from the same production lot as test samples. Equivalency mapping documented in simulation plan SP-2023-047, Section 4.3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E-measure or percent error) must be used; FEA predictions must fall within experimental variability band for both stiffness and yield load.",
      "rationale": "Mean percent error: stiffness 2.8%, yield load 3.4%. All FEA predictions fall within mean ± 2 SD of experimental results. E-measure computed per ASME V&V 20; model adequacy confirmed at the required credibility level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs predicted by the model must be directly linked to the device performance requirements cited in the regulatory submission.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness (N/mm) and yield load (N) are the performance metrics specified in the 510(k) substantial equivalence argument under 21 CFR 888.3076. Direct linkage between model QoIs and regulatory performance requirements is documented in the submission traceability matrix."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be conducted under conditions sufficiently similar to the intended use context to support extrapolation of model credibility to the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation conducted using production-representative hardware under the standardized ASTM F1717 protocol, which is the same protocol referenced in the predicate device 510(k). Geometry, material, assembly, and loading are representative of the intended clinical use loading analogue. Validation relevance to the submission context is confirmed."
    }
  ],
